The paper deals with shared autonomy, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). It also involves predicting user goals and decision-making, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The user study aspect of the paper suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a POMDP framework and optimization techniques suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. Finally, the use of maximum entropy inverse optimal control suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
